Validation of projects and programmes
* Companies or persons wishing to apply for attestations for an emission-reduction project or programme must have it validated at their own expense by a validator approved by the FOEN.
* A description of the project or programme is to be submitted to the validator. This must include information about:
* the measures for reducing emissions;
	* the technologies applied;
	* the delimitation from other climate and energy policy instruments;
	* the hypothetical progression of greenhouse gas emissions if the emission-reducing measures of the project or programme were not implemented (ref
